  "body": "<!-- This form is for bug reports and feature requests ONLY! \r\n\r\nIf you're looking for help check [Stack Overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/kubernetes) and the [troubleshooting guide](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/troubleshooting/).\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\nDue to a fix (#51279) that went into k8s v1.8, the DaemonSet scheduler now respects the termination grace period.  This results in calico/node taking longer to restart during a rolling upgrade or deletion, which delays updates to the networking dataplane during that time.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\n- Start the calico add-on on a k8s v1.8 cluster\r\n- Delete a calico/node pod.\r\n- Observe it takes a long time to be restarted (~90s)\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\nI'm about to submit a PR to reduce the grace period for calico/node.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): v1.8\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration:\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Others:\r\n",
